public class SQLResultSet<T extends JavaScriptObject>
extends JavaScriptObject

Represents the ResultSet as a result of an SQL Statement invoked by SQLTransaction.executeSql(String, Object[], StatementCallback).

Method Detail

getInsertId

public final int getInsertId()
Returns:
the row ID of the row that the SQLResultSet object's SQL statement inserted into the database, if the statement inserted a row. If the statement inserted multiple rows, the ID of the last row will be returned. If the statement did not insert a row, then this call raises a DatabaseException.

getRowsAffected

public final int getRowsAffected()
Returns:
the number of rows that were affected by the SQL statement. If the statement did not affected any rows, then the attribute returns zero. For SELECT statements, this returns zero (querying the database doesn't affect any rows).

getRows

public final SQLResultSetRowList<T> getRows()
Returns:
a SQLResultSetRowList representing the rows returned, in the order returned by the database. If no rows were returned, then the object will be empty (its length will be zero).
